response.question: What is the time complexity of linear search?
response.correct_answer: The time complexity of linear search is O(n) for the worst and average cases.
response.feedback: The student's answer is conceptually close but notationally incorrect. In Big O notation, constant factors and lower-order terms are dropped. Therefore, while the algorithm may take up to n-1 comparisons, this simplifies to O(n). The answer demonstrates an understanding of the linear nature of the search but fails to apply the formal conventions of Big O notation correctly.
